<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB: 5000, 9100, 9200, 9300, 9400 - ADJUSTMENTS - CAB AIR
        SUSPENSION (9200/9300/9400 DAY CAB MODELS)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1600519" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CAB AIR SUSPENSION (9200/9300/9400 DAY CAB MODELS)</title>
        <para>To adjust cab ride height, measure ride height between the bottom of the cab mounting bracket and the top
            of the crossmember mounting bracket (
            <hotlnk document="s16005v_44.xml" xrefid="f1600580">Figure 80</hotlnk>). If dimension does not meet
            specified height of 5-3/16 inches &#177; 1/16 (132 mm) for 9200, 9300, and 9400 day cab models with single
            bag system, adjust as necessary using the following procedure.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Have air system fully charged.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove one end of the height control valve linkage (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16005b2">Item 4, Figure 112</hotlnk>), loosen jam nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16005b2">Item 7, Figure 112</hotlnk>) and adjust accordingly. Tighten the jam nut on
                the valve linkage.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The height control valve arm (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16005b2">Item 5, Figure 112</hotlnk>) has a slot (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16005b2">Item 6, Figure 112</hotlnk>) which will allow for coarse adjustment also.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f16005b2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G16005E6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 112. Height Control Valve Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. AIR LINE (SUPPLY)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. AIR LINE (TO AIR SPRING)</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE LINKAGE</callout1>
                <callout1>5. HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE ARM</callout1>
                <callout1>6. SLOT FOR COARSE ADJUSTMENT</callout1>
                <callout1>7. JAM NUT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
